               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-794" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-794" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-794" type="surname" value="SIDNEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-794" type="given" value="WILLIAM HENRY MARLOW"></interp>WILLIAM HENRY MARLOW SIDNEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a solicitor, of Hatton-garden. I have searched at Doctors' Commons for the wills of Lady and Arthur Hubbard, but could find no such names—these documents are not copies of wills which would be sent from Doctors' Commons—they are on paper, bearing the seal of, and only used in, the Court of Chancery—I have inquired for the person mentioned in the receipt—there is no such person there.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
